-- Centrica Makes Natural Gas, Condensate Discovery in Well in Norwegian Sea
-- Meera Bhatia
-- 2010-04-23T06:53:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/faroe-petroleum-finds-up-to-95-million-barrels-equivalent-of-gas-by-norway.html

          
          
             Centrica Plc made a natural gas and
condensate discovery in a well in the Norwegian Sea, the
Norwegian Petroleum Directorate said.  
 The well proved resources of 3 million to 15 million cubic
meters of oil equivalents, the agency said in a statement.
Centrica is operator of the license and holds a 28 percent
stake.  
 Faroe Petroleum Plc, which has 15 percent, earlier
announced the discovery. E.ON AG also owns 15 percent, Petro-
Canada 30 percent and North Energy ASA 12 percent.  
